  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1164",
  "title": "More useful no-results message",
  "body": "In the [instant-search-demo built using the algoliasearch-helper](https://demo.algolia.com/examples/instant-search/jquery/), there is a neat \"no-results\" UI that contains the currently active filters.\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2853038/17312198/e12766dc-5805-11e6-9a95-0d6c9da2680c.png)\n\nUnless I missed something, recreating this with instantsearch.js requires a custom widget (the widget `currentrefinedvalues` can't be easily integrated into the no-results message).\n\nWould it be possible to have this feature handled natively by the library?\n",
